‘‘leap-ahead  technology  and  large  technology  and  so  forth’’—well, 
one  of  those  leap-ahead  technologies  is  obviously  a  plug-in  hybrid, 
which  I  talked  about  earlier.  I  mean,  if  you’ve  got  people  who  can 
drive around and get 150 miles per gallon today, why can’t we leap 
ahead  and  have  a  whole  bunch  more  of  those  vehicles  available  to 
Americans,  which  doesn’t  require  them  to  give  up  size,  to  give  up 
ability  to  take  the  kids  to  the  soccer  game,  to  do  all  the  things 
we’ve  heard  about  in  these  arguments  for  years,  but  could  do  it  at 
